Topic: Authorities in the United States say a computer hacker hacked into a water system in a Florida town and tried to add "dangerous amounts" of chemicals to the water. In Oldsmer, the hacker briefly raised the level of sodium hydroxide (lye) in the water purification system, but an employee became aware of it and stopped the practice. A small amount of sodium hydroxide is added to the water to control the acidity in the water, but it can cause major problems in the water. No arrests have been made so far and it is not clear if the man is in the United States or if he had access to the water system outside the country.
